A MAN has died following a disturbance at a flat in Glasgow.
Police and emergency services were called to the scene in the Partick area of the city shortly before 9am this morning.
Officers found the victim seriously injured at the property and, despite paramedics treating him, he died at the scene.
Another man and woman sustained minor injuries during the disturbance and were treated at the city’s Western Infirmary before being released.
Police are treating the man’s death as “suspicious”.
A spokesperson said: &quot;A post mortem will take place in due course to establish the exact cause of his death, but at this time it is being treated as suspicious.&quot;
Anyone with information is asked to contact police on 101 or Crimestoppers on 0800 555 111 where details can be given in confidence.
